install.description:
		This plugin allows for dual login from vBulletin to Joomla allowing a user to log into vBulletin and automatically be logged into Joomla. <br /><br />
		<b>PLEASE MAKE SURE JFUSION IS CONFIGURED BEFORE ENABLING THIS PLUGIN!</b><br /><br />Please do the following to add the plugin to your vBulletin installation:<br />
		1) Login to your vBulletin administrator panel<br />
		2) Click on Plugins & Products -> Add New Plugin<br />
		3) Select vbulletin as the product (usually default)<br />
		4) Select init_startup for hook location<br />
		5) Give the plugin a name such as Joomla Authentication<br />
		6) Leave execution order set at 5<br />
		7) Add the following to the php code WITH NO PHP TAGS.<br />
		If the forum is not directly beneath your Joomla install, you need to change the hook file to the appropriate path. <br />  
		<pre>
		if(!defined('_JEXEC'))
		{ 
			define('JPATH_BASE','..');  //do not add / at the end
			define('HOOK_FILE',JPATH_BASE.'/administrator/components/com_jfusion/plugins/vbulletin/hooks.php');
    		include_once(HOOK_FILE);
     		$val = "vbulletin";
     		$jFusionHook = new executeJFusionHook('init_startup',$val);
		}
		</pre> <br />
		8) Select Yes to activate the plugin <br /> 
		9) Click Save <br /><br />

		If there is a PHP error and you cannot get into your vBulletin admincp, add define('DISABLE_HOOKS', true); to your vB config, correct the plugin, and then remove it from your config.
